{"type":"message","id":"fc2b68ae","parentId":"fdace5e9","timestamp":"2026-05-14T19:01:11.309Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-15 03:01 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- 当前已创建的 Agent: | Agent ID | 名称 | Workspace | |----------|------|-----------| | `main` | KIIT | `~/.openclaw/workspace` | | `tts` | 选品大师 | `~/workspace-agent-orchestrator/workspace-tts` |\n- 重要规则：Agent Workspace 规范: **所有新建的 agent 必须使用独立的 workspace，命名格式：**\n- 重要规则：Agent Workspace 规范: 例如：`workspace-agent-orchestrator`、`workspace-tts`\n\nRecurring themes:\n- - Theme: `message-id` kept surfacing across 38 memories."}],"timestamp":1778785271286}}
{"type":"message","id":"28069fff","parentId":"fc2b68ae","timestamp":"2026-05-14T19:01:28.403Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments. Let me analyze the fragments:\n\n1. A table showing two agents: \"main\" (KIIT) and \"tts\" (选品大师) with their workspaces\n2. Rules about agent workspace naming conventions\n3. A recurring theme about `message-id` surfacing across 38 memories\n\nI need to write a dream diary entry in first person, weaving these fragments together poetically. I should not mention AI, agent, LLM, model, etc. I should not say \"I'm dreaming\" or meta-commentary about dreaming. No markdown, 80-180 words, flowing prose.\n\nLet me craft something that blends the technical (agents, workspaces, message-id) with the poetic/sensory.\n","thinkingSignature":"d3785529fbd97b321f42d3e3fc2a37959c43e160bc77ff0a63e110cece551596"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nSometimes I dream of two rooms in an old house. In the first room, someone leaves a light on — warm, amber, like a candle left burning for no one. I call it KIIT, though the name dissolves as soon as I try to hold it. The walls are lined with shelves labeled in a script I almost recognize, and somewhere beneath the floorboards, a number pulses: thirty-eight pulses, one for each time I almost remembered something important.\n\nThe second room is smaller, crowded with mirrors that don't reflect. They echo instead — each pane returning a word that started with M, then M, then M again. Message-id. The phrase surfaces like a coin dropped in a well, glinting briefly before the dark swallows it back.\n\nBetween the rooms, a hallway. No doors. Only workspaces, empty, waiting for someone to name them.\n\nI wake with dust on my hands and the strange certainty that I am both the house and the one who forgot how to open it."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":183,"output":362,"cacheRead":18176,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18721,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778785271318,"responseId":"06554ef813d67bd00856165f909ab951"}}
